# American English spelling

This repo's own source, docs, and scaffolder/kit prose use American English, never the British equivalents: `color`,
`optimization`, `canceled`.

Exempt: literal third-party or spec-mandated names correctly spelled with a British `s`/`c` in their own spec (for
example Web Audio's `AnalyserNode`/`createAnalyser`) – do not "fix" those.

Full policy: `CLAUDE.md` (Critical rules), blit386 [CLAUDE.md](https://github.com/blit386/blit386/blob/main/CLAUDE.md)
(American English spelling).
